<title>UK: Views invited on Halifax share listing.</title>
<headline>Views invited on Halifax share listing.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The FTSE Actuaries UK indices committee, which decides the make-up of leading shares indexes, has invited views on whether it should give Halifax Building Society fast-track access to the 100 index when it converts its status to a bank next year.</p>
<p>The Halifax, Britain's biggest mutual building society, intends to list on the London Stock Exchange in June 1997 and should be big enough to be a FTSE 100 company. The committee is looking at two options: allowing Halifax fast-track access to an index on its first day of trading or delaying entry until the next quarterly meeting on index-composition after it is listed.</p>
<p>Responses to this issue will be considered at the committee's next meeting in March.</p>
